theorem Topology.dense_iff_dense_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ Dense (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
  dsimp [Dense]
  constructor
  · intro hA_dense
    have h_clA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hA_dense
    have h_int : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      simpa [h_clA, interior_univ]
    simpa [h_int, closure_univ]
  · intro h_dense_int
    have h_sub :
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      Topology.closure_interior_closure_subset_closure (X := X) (A := A)
    have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      simpa [h_dense_int] using h_sub
    simpa using
      (Set.Subset.antisymm Set.Subset_univ h_univ_subset)

import Mathlib
import Aesop

open Topology

theorem Topology.denseInterior_implies_P3_fixed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior (A : Set X)) → Topology.P3 (X:=X) A := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- First, `closure (interior A)` is the whole space by density.
  have h_closure_int : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDense.closure_eq
  -- Since `interior A ⊆ A`, taking closures yields
  -- `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`, hence `closure A = univ`.
  have h_closureA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    have : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      -- Rewrite `univ` as `closure (interior A)` and use monotonicity of `closure`.
      simpa [h_closure_int] using
        (closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A))
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm this Set.Subset_univ
  -- Therefore, the interior of `closure A` is also the whole space.
  have h_interior : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closureA, interior_univ]
  -- Conclude: every point of `A` lies in `interior (closure A)`.
  simpa [h_interior] using (by
    have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by simp
    exact this)

theorem Topology.closure_inter_subset_inter_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X) ⊆ closure A ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  have hxA : x ∈ closure A :=
    (closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
  have hxB : x ∈ closure B :=
    (closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hx
  exact ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
